<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-01-20T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-01-20T19:00:00-05:00" n="631" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d631">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">893.51/7698: Telegram</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Gauss</hi></persName>)</head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-01-20T20:00:00-04:00">January 20,
                                1944—8 p.m.</date>
                        </dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>107. From the Secretary of the Treasury for Adler.</p>
                    <list>
                        <label>1.</label>
                        <item>The United States Treasury is prepared to accept the proposal
                            submitted by Dr. Kung (your 1200, July 16, 1943<note n="55" xml:id="d631fn55">
                                <ref target="frus1943China#pg_427">
                                    <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1943, China, p.
                                    427</ref>.</note>) concerning remittances to Occupied
                            China.</item>
                        <pb facs="0873" n="859" xml:id="pg_859"/>
                        <label>2.</label>
                        <item>If you perceive no objection to the adoption of Dr. Kung’s proposal,
                            you may inform him that his proposal is accepted by the United States
                            Treasury. [Morgenthau.]</item>
                    </list>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>